Package entity

Class Project

  • java.lang.Object
    • entity.Project
  • public class Project
extends java.lang.Object
    The Project class represents a housing project within the housing application system. It contains details about a specific housing project including its name, location, application period, available flat types, and the staff members associated with it. Projects can be managed by a manager and have officers assigned to them. They also have visibility settings that control whether they appear in public listings.

      • Project

        public Project​(java.lang.String projectName,
               java.lang.String neighborhood,
               java.time.LocalDate applicationStartDate,
               java.time.LocalDate applicationEndDate,
               java.util.ArrayList<FlatType> flatTypes,
               Manager manager,
               int officerSlots,
               java.util.ArrayList<Officer> assignedOfficers,
               VisibilityEnum visibility)
        Complete constructor that initializes a Project with all specified values.
        Parameters:
        projectName - The name identifier for this housing project
        neighborhood - The area or district where the project is located
        applicationStartDate - When citizens can begin applying for this project
        applicationEndDate - When the application period for this project closes
        flatTypes - List of flat types (sizes and configurations) available in this project
        manager - The manager who oversees this project
        officerSlots - Maximum number of officers that can be assigned to this project
        assignedOfficers - List of officers currently assigned to this project
        visibility - Whether the project is visible to the public or hidden
